    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="854"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-03T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 3, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 556. Repeated information Paris 9,
                    London 6, Saigon 7. <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 511.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d854fn1">Dated July 2, <ref target="#pg_1275">p. 1275</ref>.</note>
                    Thinking here appears to be generally that, if military representatives come up
                    with substantive reports within 21-day period, Ministers will meet soon
                    thereafter. Report that <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> will
                    return about July 8 fairly wide-spread. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                        >Chauvel</persName> today read <persName corresp="#p_BPW1">Bonsal</persName>
                    passage from letter he had received from <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                        >Mendes-France</persName> to effect latter anticipated meeting in Geneva at
                    ministerial level about July 12 or later with final showdown about July 19
                    (expiration of period <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> has
                    given himself to secure solution).</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> himself believes that Ministers
                    will have to take final decisions re demarcation line and re outstanding points
                    of difference re control. He thus apparently envisages meeting of Ministers here
                    before reaching of final decisions on agreement and notably before disposition
                    of some of points contained in US-<gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>.</p>
                <p>Press has asked us whether Secretary or Under Secretary planning return.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d854fn2">On this question, see telegram 101 to London, July 7,
                            <ref target="#pg_1294">p. 1294</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
